pullRequest.title: Fix sysinfo_test_get_cwd3 to handle symlinks
pullRequest.bodyText:
On z/OS the /tmp directory is typically found under /SYSTEM. On OSX,
under /private. Rather than hard coding assumptions, update the test to
determine the location of /tmp dynamically.
Before the fix:
Starting test j9sysinfo_test_get_cwd3
  mkdir /tmp/j9sysinfo_test_get_cwd3/
  cd /tmp/j9sysinfo_test_get_cwd3/
  CWD = /SYSTEM/tmp/j9sysinfo_test_get_cwd3
./si.c line 1907: j9sysinfo_test_get_cwd3 invalid directory rc: 1

		LastErrorNumber: 0
		LastErrorMessage: 

Ending test j9sysinfo_test_get_cwd3

With the fix:
Starting test j9sysinfo_test_get_cwd3
  cd /tmp/
  CWD = /SYSTEM/tmp
  expected result /SYSTEM/tmp/j9sysinfo_test_get_cwd3/
  mkdir j9sysinfo_test_get_cwd3/
  cd j9sysinfo_test_get_cwd3/
  CWD = /SYSTEM/tmp/j9sysinfo_test_get_cwd3
Ending test j9sysinfo_test_get_cwd3

nodes.bodyText:
OSX appears to have a similar issue with /tmp being /private/tmp handled above by:
#if defined(OSX)
	const char *utf8 = "/private/tmp/j9sysinfo_test_get_cwd3/";
#else /* defined(OSX) */

Can this be adapted for Z to always use /SYSTEM/tmp/j9sysinfo_test_get_cwd3/?

beforeCommit.message:
Fix sysinfo_test_get_cwd3 to handle /SYSTEM/tmp on zOS

On z/OS the /tmp directory is typically found in /SYSTEM.

Signed-off-by: Peter Shipton <Peter_Shipton@ca.ibm.com>
